page.title: 05CHRISTIAN NAMES IN WETHERBY
page.content:
At Wetherby High School, in 1985, we carried out a survey to find out the most popular boy's and girl's names in the entire School of 1170 pupils.
We started off by finding the names in individual years from 1 to 7. After finding these, they were added together to find the total within the School.
The most popular boy's names were; {Richard (37),}Mark (35), David (34) Andrew (32), Michael (20), Paul (18) Stephen (18), Simon (13), John (12) James (12), Ian (12) and Jonathan (9).
The most popular girl's names were; {Sarah (35),}Joanne (21), Catherine (18), Nicola (16), Helen (15), Sharon (14), Clare (11), Karen (11), Julie (10), Vicky (9) and Deborah (9).
